iterator

Interface Iterable<T>


  • public interface Iterable<T>

    Iterable

    The Iterable interface provides a standard way of obtaining an iterator from a collection that supports it.
    Since:
    October 05 2015
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Wolfy

    • Method Detail

      • iterator

        Iterator<T> iterator()
              throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        Creates an iterator for all elements of the current collection. This method is overloaded.
        Returns:
        Returns a new Iterator for the current collection
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An exception is thrown if the collection has no elements, or is null.

      • iterator

        Iterator<T> iterator(int startIndex)
              throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        Creates an iterator for the elements of the current collection, within the range: startIndex collection.length1. The range is inclusive on both ends. This method is overloaded.
        Parameters:
        startIndex - The startIndex. Its value should be >= 0 and < collection.length
        Returns:
        Returns a new Iterator for the current collection, within the given range.
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An Exception is thrown if the startIndex parameter is not within the ranges described above.

      • iterator

        Iterator<T> iterator(int startIndex,
                     int length)
              throws IteratorOutOfBoundsException
        Creates an iterator for the elements of the current collection, within the range: startIndex (startIndex+length)1. The range is inclusive on both ends.
        Parameters:
        startIndex - The startIndex. Its value should be >= 0 and < collection.length
        length - The length. The value of startIndex+length should be > 0 and <= collections.length
        Returns:
        Returns a new Iterator for the current collection, within the given range.
        Throws:
        IteratorOutOfBoundsException - An exception is thrown if any of the parameter values is not within the ranges described above.
